        "tl_dr": {
          "en": "Microsoft researchers, in collaboration with Princeton University and Universitat Politècnica de València, introduced ADeLe, a system designed to predict and explain AI performance across various tasks.",
          "zh": "微软研究人员与普林斯顿大学和瓦伦西亚理工大学合作，推出了ADeLe系统，旨在预测和解释人工智能在不同任务中的表现。"
        },
        "key_takeaways": {
          "en": [
            "ADeLe is a system designed to predict and explain AI performance, addressing limitations of traditional benchmarks.",
            "Traditional AI benchmarks report performance on specific tasks but provide little insight into underlying capabilities.",
            "Existing benchmarks do not explain AI failures or reliably predict outcomes on new tasks."
          ],
          "zh": [
            "ADeLe是一个旨在预测和解释人工智能性能的系统，解决了传统基准测试的局限性。",
            "传统人工智能基准测试报告特定任务的性能，但对驱动其性能的底层能力提供很少的见解。",
            "现有基准测试无法解释人工智能的故障，也无法可靠预测新任务的结果。"
          ]
        },
        "impact": {
          "en": "This development provides a method to understand AI models beyond simple performance metrics, offering insights into their underlying capabilities. This could lead to more robust and explainable AI systems, enhancing their reliability in novel applications.",
          "zh": "这一进展提供了一种超越简单性能指标来理解人工智能模型的方法，深入洞察其底层能力。这有助于开发更稳健、更具解释性的人工智能系统，从而提高它们在新应用中的可靠性。"
        },
        "source": "Microsoft Research",
